## What we are building

Multi-tenant **SaaS ERP for clothing retailers** (Egypt/MENA), branded **Ma7alyErp** / `mahalyerp.com`.

Three layers:
1. **SaaS Super Admin** — programming company: subscriptions, plans, tenant DBs, billing (Fawry/Paymob/etc.), freeze on late pay, support tickets.
2. **Tenant ERP** — per shop: full ERP on web (accounts, inventory w/ size-color, purchases, sales/POS/installments, HR, light manufacturing, reports, ETA tax).
3. **Android app** — tenant ERP on mobile + B2C marketplace (geo-sorted shops), consumer pays installments; platform commission on payments.

## Non-negotiable architecture

- **Tenant isolation:** subdomain per company (`company1.mahalyerp.com`), **separate DB per tenant**, unique usernames globally (`user@company`).
- **Branch vs warehouse:** **Branch** = only sales/purchase/POS outlet. **Warehouses** = storage/transfers only; never appear on sales/purchase screens.
- **Season** flows through purchases, sales, reports, reorder logic (active season from admin).
- **Concurrent users:** unlimited user records; login limited by subscription count with clear Arabic message.
- **UI:** black gradient sidebar, Cairo + table font Times New Roman bold, RTL Arabic + LTR English, ~80% screens = standard CRUD pattern (drawer, export, columns, advanced filter). References: Stockifly, CoreUI, AdminLTE. Two dashboards: owner metrics + user quick-access home.

## Clothing-specific modules (priority custom logic)

- Purchase invoice: supplier+season, matrix size/color, smart search, side drawer product create.
- Reorder threshold (% of inbound sold) → alerts → purchase order PDF → WhatsApp → PO tracking.
- Supplier occasion discount (okazion) vs general promotions (sales price only).
- Orders (pre-scan barcodes) → load into sale/transfer/returns/stock count.
- Stock count/reconciliation vs ledger.
- POS: fullscreen, tabs (sale / exchange / collect), multi-payment, installment plans, multi-seller per invoice, auto transfer if insufficient stock.
- Shifts/cash drawer → treasury handoff.
- Customer: guarantors, installment collection & restructuring, late-payment bulk SMS/WhatsApp.
- Expenses split: supplier payments | general | payroll+advances.

## Current codebase vs spec

Frontend prototype only (React/Vite): partial UI (Home, Dashboard, Departments, Purchases mock). **No backend, no SaaS, no real DB, no Android.** Extend UI toward spec; new backend/tenant model is separate work.

## When implementing

1. Read relevant PDF section + `docs/MAHALY-ERP-SPEC.md` before new features.
2. Match existing UI patterns (sidebar, i18n ar/en, CRUD shell).
3. Do not assume Gemini/API — not required for ERP.
